{"id":4295,"date":"2024-01-24T09:14:46","date_gmt":"2024-01-24T09:14:46","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/?p=4295"},"modified":"2024-01-24T09:14:46","modified_gmt":"2024-01-24T09:14:46","slug":"mern-stack-is-full-stack","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/mern-stack-is-full-stack\/","title":{"rendered":"Mern Stack Is Full Stack"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<div class=\"wp-block-rank-math-toc-block\" id=\"rank-math-toc\" id=\"rank-math-toc\"><p>Table of Contents<\/p><nav><ul><li ><a href=\"#mern-stack-is-full-stack\">Mern Stack Is Full Stack<\/a><\/li><li ><a href=\"#faq-mern-stack-is-full-stack\">FAQ- Mern Stack Is Full Stack<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/nav><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"mern-stack-is-full-stack\">Mern Stack Is Full Stack<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The MERN stack is a full-stack development solution that encompasses four key technologies: MongoDB, Express.js, React, and Node.js. This comprehensive stack covers both the frontend and backend aspects of web development. MongoDB serves as the database, Express.js manages server-side logic, React handles the frontend, and Node.js provides the runtime environment. Together, these components create a robust and cohesive framework for building modern and scalable web applications across the entire stack.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"faq-mern-stack-is-full-stack\">FAQ- Mern Stack Is Full Stack<\/h2>\n\n\n<div id=\"rank-math-faq\" class=\"rank-math-block\">\n<div class=\"rank-math-list \">\n<div id=\"faq-question-1702377048278\" class=\"rank-math-list-item\">\n<h4 class=\"rank-math-question \">Q1. Is MERN a full-stack or stack?<\/h4>\n<div class=\"rank-math-answer \">\n\n<p>Ans. The MERN stack works great for smaller projects like single-page apps or mobile apps. Full-stack developers, who are skilled in all aspects of software development, use MERN Stack mainly for web development.<\/p>\n\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div id=\"faq-question-1702377056813\" class=\"rank-math-list-item\">\n<h4 class=\"rank-math-question \">Q2. What is the full form of MERN?<\/h4>\n<div class=\"rank-math-answer \">\n\n<p>Ans. The MERN stack, which stands for MongoDB, Express, React.js, and Node.js, is a variant that replaces the traditional Angular.js with React.js in the front-end framework. Another variation is MEVN (MongoDB, Express, Vue, Node), but essentially, any front-end JavaScript framework can be used.<\/p>\n\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div id=\"faq-question-1702377072400\" class=\"rank-math-list-item\">\n<h4 class=\"rank-math-question \">Q3. Is MEAN stack and full-stack same?<div jsname=\"Q8Kwad\" class=\"aj35ze\" style=\"background-image: url(&quot;data:image\/svg+xml,<svg focusable=\\&quot;false\\&quot; xmlns=\\&quot;http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\\&quot; viewBox=\\&quot;0 0 24 24\\&quot;&gt;<path fill=\\&quot;%2370757a\\&quot; d=\\&quot;M16.59 8.59L12 13.17 7.41 8.59 6 10l6 6 6-6z\\&quot;&gt;<\/path&gt;<\/svg&gt;&quot;); display: inline-block; height: 24px; width: 24px; color: rgb(32, 33, 36); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: medium; font-weight: 400; white-space-collapse: collapse;\"><\/div><\/h4>\n<div class=\"rank-math-answer \">\n\n<p>Ans. &#8220;Full-stack&#8221; primarily refers to the developer&#8217;s role, while MEAN stack is an acronym for a comprehensive framework covering both frontend and backend. Both concepts are widely popular, and there&#8217;s a high demand for full-stack developers.<\/p>\n\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Mern Stack Is Full Stack The MERN stack is a full-stack development solution that encompasses four key technologies: MongoDB, Express.js, React, and Node.js. This comprehensive stack covers both the frontend and backend aspects of web development. MongoDB serves as the database, Express.js manages server-side logic, React handles the frontend, and Node.js provides the runtime environment. &#8230; <a title=\"Mern Stack Is Full Stack\" class=\"read-more\" href=\"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/mern-stack-is-full-stack\/\" aria-label=\"More on Mern Stack Is Full Stack\">Read more<\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":4,"featured_media":4297,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[736],"tags":[780],"class_list":["post-4295","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-mern-stack","tag-mern-stack-is-full-stack","generate-columns","tablet-grid-50","mobile-grid-100","grid-parent","grid-33"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/4295"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/4"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=4295"}],"version-history":[{"count":3,"href":"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/4295\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":6481,"href":"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/4295\/revisions\/6481"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/4297"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=4295"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=4295"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=4295"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}